HEADWORD: Subagent
<hw>Sub*a"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A
person employed by an agent to transact the whole, or a part, of the
business intrusted to the latter.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.
Chitty.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

